Deploying Spring Boot App on AWS EC2 - Commands & Descriptions

‚úÖ 1. Upload JAR to EC2
scp -i <your-key.pem> demo.jar ec2-user@<public-ip>:/home/ec2-user/






‚ö°Ô∏è 2. SSH into EC2 Instance
Linux/Mac:
ssh -i <your-key.pem> ec2-user@<public-ip>


Windows (Using PowerShell or CMD):
Open PowerShell


Navigate to the folder containing your .pem file


Run:


ssh -i .\your-key.pem ec2-user@<public-ip>


Windows (Using PuTTY):
Convert .pem to .ppk using PuTTYgen


Open PuTTY


Set Host Name: ec2-user@<public-ip>


Go to Connection > SSH > Auth


Browse and select .ppk file


Click Open to connect



üì¶ 3. Install Java (Amazon Linux 2, Java 17)
sudo yum update -y
sudo amazon-linux-extras enable corretto17
sudo yum install java-17-amazon-corretto -y
java -version



üöÄ 4. Run Spring Boot JAR with nohup
nohup java -jar demo.jar > output.log 2>&1 &


Explanation:
nohup: Prevents the app from stopping after logout


> output.log: Saves app logs


2>&1: Also saves error logs


&: Runs in background



